            MCDONNELL DOUGLAS INFORMATION SYSTEMS GROUP

                      ADMINISTRATIVE BULLETIN


No. ISG-86-80                                      7 August 1986


To:           All ISG Employees

Subject:      STATUS OF ISG MERIT REVIEW PROGRAM AND EMPLOYEE 
              SAVINGS PLAN

                                                                   


In the past few months, there has been considerable discussion 
over two ISG-wide issues:

    o    When will merit increases be reinstated?

    o    What changes, if any, will be made in the ISG Employee 
         Savings Plan?

The purpose of this memo is to let you know where things stand 
regarding these issues.

We plan to resume ISG's merit review program in January 1987.  
While I cannot provide details just yet, I can assure you that 
whatever process we use will address the fact that some 
individuals have gone longer than others without a merit review.  
I realize that the suspension of such review has been, at best, a 
major inconvenience for all of us.  However, it really has 
bettered our chances of achieving ISG's earnings objective.  I'm 
counting on your continued patience until we've finished the job 
we set out to do this year.

As for the ISG Employee Savings Plan, you received word several 
months ago that we were considering changes in the way matching 
contributions are handled.  After careful study, however, we have 
decided to make no changes in the plan at this time.



Jeremy J. Causley
Group Executive Officer


