To:           MDCSC & MDFSC Lists A-G, ISG List A-E, MDC List A-C

Subject:      NEW ASSIGNMENT/PROMOTION FOR BILL FREEMAN

                                                                   

It gives me great pleasure to announce the promotion of Bill 
Freeman, currently Director of Business Management, Computer 
Systems in MDISI.  Effective August 11, Bill will assume the 
position of Vice President, Research and Development for the 
Computer Systems Company.  Bill will be based at CSC headquarters 
in Newport Beach, California and will report to myself.  The 
following individuals will report to Bill:

    Steve Vernon, Vice President, UK Development
    Bill Schrader, Vice President, US Development
    Frank Reinhart, Vice President, Advanced Product Development

Bill's extensive background in sales, marketing, and business 
management within the computer industry over the past 12 years has 
provided him with the skills that I feel are important to the task 
of coordinating our internal worldwide engineering functions as 
well as coordinating with the sales and marketing entities which 
distribute our products.  Bill's experience in his most recent 
role of translating MDISI market needs into specific product 
development requirements will be invaluable to this effort as 
well.

I feel that this level of coordination will allow us to remain 
competitive by targeting our efforts on products to meet the needs 
and demands of our internal and external clients.  Through the 
coordinated efforts of this organization with the worldwide 
manufacturing organization under Greg Lawson (Vice President, 
Manufacturing), CSC will be even better positioned to deliver high 
quality competitive products.


Otis H. Brinkley
President
McDonnell Douglas
Computer Systems Company

Concurrence:

J. J. Causley
Group Executive Officer


